H3.text: what breed of cat has spots and stripes. tabby

A4.text: The Bengal cat is the only domestic breed of cat that has rosette markings.

A5.text: Domestic cats have four distinct and heritable coat patterns – ticked, mackerel, blotched, and spotted – these are collectively referred to as tabby markings.

A6.text: The Egyptian Mau is one of the few naturally spotted breeds of domesticated cat.

A7.text: The Egyptian Mau's coat contains dark patterns of varying size and shape, located all over the body and limbs. They also may have a stripe running down the lower spine and tail.
